overview: The user initiated a request to evaluate an existing sleep
  questionnaire application against a Statement of Work. The primary goal was to
  integrate a database for storing questionnaire responses, develop a
  client-facing dashboard for data access, and establish a simple authentication
  mechanism. After an initial codebase review, it was determined that while the
  questionnaire logic and PDF generation were complete, database storage, data
  retrieval (CSV), and an admin dashboard with authentication were missing.
  Through clarification questions, the user opted for a simple password-based
  authentication system and a combined approach for demographic data collection.
  The resulting plan outlines the steps to update the demographic fields, create
  a Prisma model for questionnaire responses, implement API endpoints for data
  submission and retrieval (including CSV export), build a basic admin login and
  dashboard, and integrate the database saving into the questionnaire's
  submission flow. NeonDB was confirmed as the suitable database choice.
